replies.bodyText: servlet will NOT be updated to io.openliberty prefix.  It is special because we need to support tolerates for servlet through 5.0.  el and jsp though can be updated yes.
replies.author: jhanders34

timeline.bodyText: Should have eeCompatible-9.0 as one of the dependent features.

replies.bodyText: You are missing the backslash to join the servlet-5.0 and eeCompatible both being features.

timeline.bodyText: This seems unnecessary.  You can just add to websocket-2.0 to the EE9_FEATURES_ARRAY in this class.  You will also need to update the ee7 and ee8 array though to included websocket-1.x there as well.
